The term '''Infovore''' depicts a person who indulges in and desires information gathering and interpretation.

''Infovore'' was introduced as a scientific term by [[neuroscience|neuroscientist]] [[Irving Biederman]] to describe the innate desire of humans to acquire, interprete and understand information.

The opposite of ''infovore'' is [[ignotarian]].

